                "uuid": "a01b4dfd-cbce-57a0-a6b2-59f657f2fdb6",
                "control-id": "pci-dss-10-2-1",
                "description": "Splunk use case UC-22.35.1 provides partial assurance in mode 'satisfies' for PCI-DSS v4.0 clause 10.2.1. Rationale: PCI 10.2.1 requires that audit logs are enabled and active for all system components; this UC detects loss of telemetry but does not validate 10.2.1's sub-requirements (10.2.1.1-10.2.1.7) for specific event types.",
